interactions.lmstext: Choose one INCORRECT statement regarding the uterine cycle.

choices.lmstext: The secretory phase of the uterine cycle is stimulated primarily by rising estrogen levels.
During the proliferative phase, the functional zone of the endometrium regenerates from the basal zone.
The proliferative phase of the uterine cycle coincides with the follicular phase of the ovarian cycle.
The bases of the uterine glands remain intact following menstruation.

interactions.lmstext: 2. Choose one INCORRECT statement regarding the follicular phase of the ovarian cycle.

choices.lmstext: Between individuals, it's duration is reliably 14 days long.
In a given cycle, while many primordial follicles become primary follicles, usually only one becomes a tertiary follicle.
Thecal cells are derived from the stroma surrounding the follicle.

interactions.lmstext: Which of the following statements is true of the basal layer of the endometrium, but not its functional layer?

choices.lmstext: It contains the cells that replace the surface epithelium after menstruation.
It goes through regular cycles of thickening and shedding.
It relies primarily on the spiral arteries for its blood supply.

interactions.lmstext: Choose one INCORRECT statement regarding the structure / function of the uterine tubes.

choices.lmstext: Their outermost layer is an adventitia.
The ovum is nourished by the secretions of the ovarian mucosa.
The Fallopian tube opens into the peritoneal cavity.
Peristaltic contraction of its muscularis propels fluid and the ovum toward the uterus.
